I was trying to reverse a series of comma-separated elements. I tried this code:
```rust

macro_rules! test1 {
    ([] $($reversed:ident)*) => {
        ;
    };
    ([$first:ident $($rest:ident)*] $($reversed:ident)*) => {
        test1!([$($rest)*] $first $($reversed)*)
    };
}

macro_rules! test2 {
    ([] $($reversed:ident),*) => {
        ;
    };
    ([$first:ident, $($rest:ident),*] $($reversed:ident),*) => {
        test2!([$($rest),*] $first, $($reversed),*)
    };
}
fn test() {
    test1!([a b]);
    test2!([a,b]);
}
```

I expected to see this happen: 
In this example, test1 is one that I got from [stackoverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/42171483/how-to-recursively-take-the-last-argument-of-a-macro/42174800#42174800), but it only supports space as separatiion. So I modified test 1 to support comma. 

Instead, this happened: 
However test2 cannot compile, whatever I do.

